This paper is about enabling a robot to learn tabletop object manipulation by imitation, which falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of reinforcement learning (RL) and segmentation of demonstrations, which are common topics in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of external observations, which could involve computer vision techniques (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses the interaction of the robot with the world, which could involve control systems (cs.SY).
